args: I find it so reassuring to have the\nDragon Scion fighting at our side.
Ain't that the truth! With her help,\nwe'll have these fiends mopped up\nfaster'n I can eat a ham sandwich.
Hee hee! Let's move on to theâ€”
Right as rain, thanks to Mym.
I'm glad. And on another happy note,\nI think we're done with the fiends here.
Ha! We took 'em out like CHAMPS!\nEven though Tiki did get a weeeee\nbit careless there in her dragon form.
Oops! Sorry about that. But I'm still\nreally grateful for your help, Mym.
So long as you don't let your guard down\nnext time, there is nothing to be sorry for.
Heh. They're like a pair of sisters.
Hmm, yes. The reliable older sister and\nthe perky, yet open little sister.
Plus they can both turn into dragons!\nEr, or turn into people? Never mind.\nYou all know what I mean!
Hell, at this rate, they might as well\ngo ahead and make it official.
Oh my gosh, I would LOVE to have\nMym be my big sister for real!
Er, don't you like the idea?
It's not that I don't LIKE it.\nIt's more that...
Well, you're actually older than me,\nso isn't it odd for me to be considered\nthe big sister in this relationship?
Oh, I don't think it's that weird.\nYou're more mature than me in\na whole lot of ways.
Your human form is incredibly strong,\nand you just know so much STUFF!
Also, you're kind, and you're beautiful,\nand your dragon form is super cute!
So that, plus a million more reasons,\nis why you should be the big sister.
Normally I enjoy compliments, but this is\nbeing laid on a bit thick even for me...
Besides, the idea of my family getting\nlarger makes me really happy.
In terms of my dragonkin family,\nI have no one except old Ban-Ban.
Mmm, that's right. The rest of Tiki's\nkindâ€”the Divine Dragonsâ€”all perished.
(We always have to say goodbye some\nday, but it's still so sad when the time\ncomes...)
(I know the way to keep that feeling\nat bay is through meeting new people.\nSo in that case...)
Right, then! I've made up my mind!
From this day forward, you will be the\nlittle sister of Brunhilda the Flamewyrm!
Yay! Thank you so much, Big Sis!
No one's ever called me that before...

(It makes my heart race in a totally
different way than being called loving
names by my darling. I guess this is what
it means to be someone's big sister.)
Hey, Tiki? Would you call me\nï¼‚big sisï¼‚ one more time?
Of course! Anything for my big sis!
(Eee! So cute! I'm going to be the best\nbig sister the world has ever seen...)
Yo, Mym. You okay in there?\nYou look a little lost in thought.
All of you may ALSO refer to me\nas your big sister!
Oh, that's great! Now EVERYONE\nis my brother or sister!
Judging from how eager she appears,\nI would say Mym is going to make a\nlovely older sister.
Er, does anybody else think she's kinda\ngettin' the wrong idea here...?
